<TITLE> Experts to file report on Padma Bridge Thursday: minister </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 28 (bdnews24.com)Experts will submit the project inception report along with a presentation on what the proposed Padma Bridge will be like on Thursday, the communication minister said Tuesday. The bridge is expected to be complete by 2013, Syed Abul Hossain said while inaugurating a postgraduate certificate course on 'Management of land acquisition, resettlement and rehabilitation' organised by BRAC University. The Padma Bridge will be built over Shariatpur, Madaripur and Munshiganj districts, the minister said. "The volume of land to be affected due to the bridge construction in Madaripur district has already been assessed and the government has been notified about it," Hossain said. The government will soon be provided with information on the land to be acquired in Shariatpur and Munshiganj districts, he added. Justin Lee, the Australian high commissioner in Bangladesh, said, "Australia has all along been working with Bangladesh government and BRAC is providing assistance in achieving their national, institutional and millennium development goals." BRAC Development Institute and Department of Architecture, BRAC University have jointly organised the three-month course starting on May 17. The course has been sponsored by the World Bank, DFID and USAID. Syed A Hashemi, chairman of BRAC Development Institute, presided over the event. The university's vice chancellor Jamilur Reza Chowdhury was present. bdnew
